<section xml:id="S_shortcuts">
  <title>Keyboard Shortcuts</title>
  <idx><h>shortcuts</h></idx>
  <idx><h>keyboard shortcuts</h></idx>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      You may be able to use your computer fine without any shortcuts. But wow, do they make your life easier. This section could go in an appendix but I think it is so important to know at many shortcuts as possible to help you use your computer faster. I use shortcuts every day in my web browser, programming software, documents editing software (e.g., Microsoft Word), and just my computer in general. I have tried to break up the following shortcuts by the keys needed. <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>F</kbd> works well on this page.
    </p>
    <p>
      Note: Windows uses <kbd>Control</kbd> 
      (or <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>) as the <q>main</q> button whereas Mac usually uses <kbd>Command</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd</kbd>). I regularly use a Mac and Google Chrome so many of these might be more accurate and detailed for Chrome and Mac users.
    </p>
  </introduction>

