  <subsection xml:id="SS_shortcut_vscode">
    <title><init>VS</init> Code Shortcuts</title>
    
    <p>
      This part lists many useful shortcuts with work in <init>VS</init> Code. Most should work in both Windows and Mac, but any differences are noted.
    </p>

    <tabular halign='center'>
      <col width='10%'/>
      <col width='10%'/>
      <col width='30%'/>
      <col width='50%'/>
      <row header='yes' bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'>Base Key(s)</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Variable Key</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Function</p></cell>
        <cell><p>Notes</p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Alt</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Click</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Create multiple cursors (each click is one cursor)</p></cell>
        <cell><p>Useful for changing multiple occurances at once</p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Alt</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd></cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Click and Drag</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Create a vertical line of cursors</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>`</kbd></cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Open the terminal window</p></cell>
        <cell><p>Macs should also use <kbd>Ctrl</kbd></p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Move cursor to extreme edge</p></cell>
        <cell><p>For instance, the up arrow will take you to the very top of the file and the left arrow will take you to the very left of the line</p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>Alt</kbd></cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Left/Right arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Navigate between open files</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>Alt</kbd></cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Up/Down arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Create new cursor above/below the current cursor</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd></cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Left/Right arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Select content to extreme edge</p></cell>
        <cell><p>For instance, the up arrow will select everything up to the very top of the file and the left arrow will select everything over to the very left of the line</p></cell>
      </row>
      
      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Alt</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Left/Right arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Move cursor to beginning/end of each work</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Alt</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Up/Down arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Move current line up/down</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Alt</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Z</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Force line breaks</p></cell>
        <cell>Works for lines that go off screen. Makes these lines default to start back at the beginning, while keeping the content on the same line.</cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Shift</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Left/Right arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Select one character at a time to the left/right</p></cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Shift</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Up/Down arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Select one row at a time up/down</p></cell>
        <cell><p>Selects based on current position of cursor</p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> +</cell>
        <cell right='minor'>Arrows</cell>
        <cell right='minor'><p>Move cursor to extreme edge</p></cell>
        <cell><p>For instance, the up arrow will take you to the very top of the file and the left arrow will take you to the very left of the line</p></cell>
      </row>

      <row bottom='minor'>
        <cell right='minor'><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> or <kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd></cell>
